"{\"uid\": \"flotrack.org-articles-12759140-grant-fisher-becomes-first-american-to-win-olympic-10k-medal-since-2012\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"TRE LIVE  PSU T&F Winter Classic  GVSU Holiday Open  St. Jude Memphis Marathon  BU Sharon Colyear-Danville Season Opener  Springfield T&F Season Opener  Spartan Alumni Holiday Retreat  River Hawk Early Season Invite  Valencia Marathon  Holiday Kickoff Open  Tiffin Track Meet #1  Brooks XC Championships  The Marathon Project  Phoenix Track & Field Invite  Kaye & JJ Smith Invitational  For the first time since 2012, an American stood on the 10,000m Olympic podium.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 466, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 327, \"end\": 334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phoenix_Raceway\", \"score\": 0.9999999757203571, \"rank\": 2.4276398402886705e-08, \"text\": \"Phoenix\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phoenix_Raceway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phoenix_Raceway\"}, {\"begin\": 335, \"end\": 348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Track_and_field\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.4395865666438883e-41, \"text\": \"Track & Field\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Track_and_field\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Track_and_field\"}, {\"begin\": 421, \"end\": 429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9784789403094014, \"rank\": 0.016713653763536777, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Friday, Grant Fisher won Olympic bronze by putting together one of the gutsiest races of his career, only finishing behind winner Joshua Cheptegei and Ethiopia's Berihu Aregawi.\", \"from\": 468, \"to\": 648, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 479, \"end\": 491, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grant_Fisher\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Grant Fisher\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grant_Fisher\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grant_Fisher\"}, {\"begin\": 601, \"end\": 617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joshua_Cheptegei\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Joshua Cheptegei\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joshua_Cheptegei\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joshua_Cheptegei\"}, {\"begin\": 622, \"end\": 630, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.999999300259805, \"rank\": 6.966776106088573e-07, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}, {\"begin\": 633, \"end\": 647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berihu_Aregawi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Berihu Aregawi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berihu_Aregawi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berihu_Aregawi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fisher became the first American to win a medal in the 10K since 2012, mirroring Galen Rupp's performance in London when he won silver in 27:30.90.\", \"from\": 650, \"to\": 797, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 674, \"end\": 682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9784789403094014, \"rank\": 0.016713653763536777, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 731, \"end\": 741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Galen_Rupp\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Galen Rupp\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Galen_Rupp\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Galen_Rupp\"}, {\"begin\": 759, \"end\": 765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999995325518922, \"rank\": 3.118011691975578e-07, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Uganda's Cheptegei, who is the world record holder in the event, stopped the clock and won gold in an Olympic record of 26:43.14, while the Ethiopian Aregawi won silver in 26:43.44.\", \"from\": 799, \"to\": 980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 799, \"end\": 805, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\", \"score\": 0.9999999446611143, \"rank\": 4.775678344289605e-08, \"text\": \"Uganda\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\"}, {\"begin\": 939, \"end\": 948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopians\", \"score\": 0.9781273220840807, \"rank\": 0.02236117734077323, \"text\": \"Ethiopian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fisher was in line for a runner-up placement before he was passed in the final meter.\", \"from\": 982, \"to\": 1067, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But the former NCAA champion from Stanford kept himself in contention throughout the entirety of the chaotic 25 laps, never letting himself fall out of the top-five, despite getting tripped up somewhere in the middle.\", \"from\": 1069, \"to\": 1286, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1084, \"end\": 1097, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999999985109298, \"rank\": 1.4884793122631552e-09, \"text\": \"NCAA champion\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 1103, \"end\": 1111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\", \"score\": 0.999999641566156, \"rank\": 3.251834848182563e-07, \"text\": \"Stanford\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He also turned his ankle late in the race, stepping on the race.\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1352, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With just under 150m to go, Fisher took advantage of his prime position and made his move, surging all the way into second, before getting out-leaned at the line, crossing in 26:43.46.\", \"from\": 1354, \"to\": 1538, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1382, \"end\": 1388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Derek_Fisher\", \"score\": 0.9197447737068551, \"rank\": 0.05005597188739878, \"text\": \"Fisher\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Derek_Fisher\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Derek_Fisher\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the fastest 10,000m in Olympic history, Fisher closed in just around 55 seconds, avenging his fifth-place finish in Tokyo, where the race also came down to a blistering final lap.\", \"from\": 1540, \"to\": 1722, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1583, \"end\": 1589, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Derek_Fisher\", \"score\": 0.9197447737068551, \"rank\": 0.05005597188739878, \"text\": \"Fisher\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Derek_Fisher\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Derek_Fisher\"}, {\"begin\": 1659, \"end\": 1664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.8920738260278837, \"rank\": 0.1205344230585534, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His final 1,000 meters was recorded in about 2:27.\", \"from\": 1723, \"to\": 1773, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The American record holder will be back on the track in just a few days time, as the first round of the 5,000m is slated for Wednesday, August 7.\", \"from\": 1775, \"to\": 1920, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1779, \"end\": 1787, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9784789403094014, \"rank\": 0.016713653763536777, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics begin on July 26 and end on August 11.\", \"from\": 1922, \"to\": 1973, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The track and field events will begin on Aug. 1.\", \"from\": 1974, \"to\": 2022, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Do not miss all the track and field season action streaming on FloTrack.Check out the FloTrack schedule for more events.\", \"from\": 2024, \"to\": 2144, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Video footage from each event will be archived and stored in a video library for FloTrack subscribers to watch for the duration of their subscriptions.\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2297, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tags:  Get the most important Track & Field stories delivered straight to your inbox.\", \"from\": 2301, \"to\": 2386, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2331, \"end\": 2344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Track_and_field\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.4395865666438883e-41, \"text\": \"Track & Field\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Track_and_field\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Track_and_field\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a92006 - Present FloSports, Inc. All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 2388, \"to\": 2440, \"entities\": []}]}"